# Commit Messages

When a change addresses an issue, include `Closes #<issue>` in the commit body so the PR's Related issues section can reference it and GitHub auto-closes on merge.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<description>

Closes #<issue>
```

Use `Closes`, `Fixes`, or `Resolves` followed by ` #<issue>`.

## Examples

- `feat: add X` (no issue)
- `fix: resolve bug\n\nCloses #42`
- `docs: update guide\n\nCloses #123`
